```
https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Oswald:wght@400;600;700&family=Archivo:wght@400;600;700;800&family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,400;0,9..40,500;0,9..40,600&display=swap
```

### Visual Language

- **Layout:** Full-bleed sections; 1440px max-width container; 80px vertical section padding on desktop, 48px on mobile.
- **Imagery:** Real construction photos via Pexels/Unsplash CDN URLs embedded inline (researcher to confirm best URLs; demo-builder may fallback to CSS-gradient placeholder cards with construction icons if CDN is unreliable).
- **Video (hero):** Royalty-free construction B-roll looped as CSS `object-fit: cover` video. See "Video Sourcing" section below.
- **Cards:** 4px border-radius, subtle border (`#2A2F38`), soft box-shadow on hover. No flashy gradients on cards, just clean surfaces.
- **Buttons:** Amber fill, black text, 0px radius (sharp corners convey industrial strength). Secondary: transparent with amber border.
- **Dividers / accents:** Thin amber line (`3px solid #E8991A`) used as section accent left-border or horizontal rule before headings.
- **Motion:** Fade-in + slight translateY on scroll (IntersectionObserver). Counter animation on stats. Lightbox fade. Hamburger morph. All gated by `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- **Icons:** Inline SVG (no icon font dependency). Simple construction-themed icons for services.

---

## Hero Video Sourcing

**Primary approach:** Embed a royalty-free MP4 directly in the `<video>` tag using a reliable CDN.

Recommended free sources (researcher/demo-builder picks one working URL):
1. **Mixkit** (mixkit.co) — free stock video, direct MP4 download allowed. Search: "construction site aerial" or "excavator working" or "building construction workers."
   - Example URL pattern: `https://assets.mixkit.co/videos/preview/mixkit-<id>-large.mp4`
2. **Pexels Video API** — direct MP4 URLs available from pexels.com video pages for free.
3. **Pixabay** — same model.

**Implementation:**
```html
<video class="hero-video" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="assets/hero-poster.jpg">
  <source src="<CDN_URL>.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>
```

**Fallback:** If the CDN video cannot be embedded (CORS or load failure), the poster image `assets/hero-poster.jpg` shows (a dark construction site photo), and the amber gradient overlay + headline remain fully readable. The JS `hero.js` handles the error case and removes the `<video>` element gracefully, showing the fallback poster as a full-viewport background image.

**Poster image:** A dark, dramatic construction-site image fetched from Unsplash via URL (no download needed):
`https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504307651254-35680f356dfd?w=1920&q=80` (aerial construction site, dark tones).

**Overlay:** Linear gradient `from rgba(0,0,0,0.82) left to rgba(0,0,0,0.35) right` ensures white text is always readable regardless of video frame.

