## Scope Fences (what is NOT in this demo)

- No real backend or form submission endpoint (contact form uses client-side success state only)
- No CMS or editable content
- No real company video (royalty-free CDN video or graceful fallback)
- No real project photos in file system (Unsplash CDN URLs embedded in HTML/JS)
- No login or user accounts
- No analytics, chat widget, or third-party integrations

These are deliberate omissions for a proposal demo, not gaps. The proposal will note the full production version would include a backend form handler, CMS integration, and real brand assets.

---

## Build Notes for demo-builder

1. **Video tag:** Set `poster` to an Unsplash construction image URL (dark, dramatic). Set `src` to a Mixkit MP4. In `main.js`, listen for `video.addEventListener('error', ...)` and fall back to showing the poster as background-image on the hero container.

2. **Copy tone:** Confident, regional, trustworthy. No jargon overload. First-person plural ("We build..."). No em-dashes, no en-dashes.

3. **CSS custom properties:** Define all palette, type scale, and spacing tokens at `:root` in `style.css` so they are easy to scan and override.

4. **Counter animation:** Simple RAF loop from 0 to target value over ~1.5s. Use `easeOutQuad` easing. Guard with `prefers-reduced-motion` check (if reduced, just set final value immediately).

5. **Filter logic (projects.js):** Each project card has a `data-category` attribute. Filter tabs toggle an `active` class and set a `data-filter` attribute on the grid container. CSS rule: `.projects-grid[data-filter="residential"] .project-card:not([data-category="residential"]) { display: none; }`. This is instant and requires no animation for correctness, though a brief opacity fade is nice if motion is allowed.

6. **Lightbox:** Maintain an array of project objects. On card click, find the index in the array, set `currentIndex`, render into the modal. Left/right arrows cycle through `currentIndex`. ESC key listener on `document.addEventListener('keydown', ...)`. Trap focus within modal while open (WCAG).

7. **Form validation:** Validate on both `blur` (individual field) and `submit` (all fields). Show error messages in a `<span class="field-error">` below each input. On valid submit, replace `.contact-form` with `.contact-success` div (CSS class toggle, no page reload).

8. **Responsive nav:** At 768px, hide the desktop links, show the hamburger button. Hamburger click toggles `.nav-open` on `<nav>`. CSS handles the drawer positioning and transition. Click outside (document click listener, check `!nav.contains(event.target)`) closes the drawer.

9. **Section scroll animations:** `IntersectionObserver` with `threshold: 0.15`. Add `.visible` class when element enters viewport. CSS: `.fade-in { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(24px); transition: opacity 0.5s ease, transform 0.5s ease; } .fade-in.visible { opacity: 1; transform: none; }`. Guard in JS: if `prefers-reduced-motion`, add `.visible` immediately to all elements.

10. **Active nav link:** In each HTML file's `<nav>`, add `class="active"` to the correct link. Do not rely on JS for this (avoids flash of unstyled nav on load).

